OL,3,C'You saved my life' - abused woman
OL,4,Cmeets police staff she says rescued her
OL,6,FCall handler Emma picked up her pleas
OL,7,Ffor help and sent officers who started
OL,8,Fthe investigation that saw Ben Fitton
OL,9,Fjailed for 18 years in 2024.
OL,11,FHannah waived the right to anonymity
OL,12,Fthat all victims of sex assault are
OL,13,Fentitled to, in order to try to
OL,14,Fencourage other women to come forward.
OL,16,FShe wanted to meet the woman who first
OL,17,Fmade her feel safe, and this time
OL,18,Fwords didn't seem enough as she
OL,19,Fthanked Emma, whispering 'you were
OL,20,Fpart of saving my life, you do such an
OL,21,Fincredible job.'
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
